 :tx/rationale "CRDT SYNC as external mutation model — the daemon is a CRDT replica, not a filesystem watcher. The store is a G-Set CvRDT (INV-STORE-001). Merge is set union, commutative, associative, idempotent. The daemon holds Store_daemon in memory; disk holds Store_disk. Periodic sync: daemon lists txns/ for files newer than its frontier, applies them via apply_tx. This IS the merge operation — same algebraic structure as multi-agent merge (INV-MERGE-001). No inotify, no OS-specific APIs, no missed events, no race conditions. The daemon is just another replica that periodically pulls. Sync trigger: every 5-10s background, or on-demand before consistency-critical operations. ArcSwap<Arc<Store>> (ADR-STORE-018) provides snapshot isolation — readers never blocked by sync. This is the most axiologically aligned solution because it uses the system's own coordination primitive (CRDT merge) rather than introducing an external mechanism (filesystem events)."
